      "sectionId": "masculine",
      "title": "Masculine Nouns",
      "explanation": "Most Russian masculine nouns end in a consonant: кот (cat), дом (house), стол (table), хлеб (bread). Some end in -ь: день (day), словарь (dictionary). Nouns referring to males ending in -а/-я are also masculine: папа (dad), дядя (uncle).",
      "tip": "Ends in a consonant? Probably masculine!",
      "examples": [
        {
          "ru": "Кот",
          "en": "Cat (masculine)",
          "highlight": "Кот"
        },
        {
          "ru": "Стол",
          "en": "Table (masculine)",
          "highlight": "Стол"
        },
        {
          "ru": "Папа",
          "en": "Dad (masculine)",
          "highlight": "Папа"
        }
      ],
